          "type": "text",
          "text": "1. Overview"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The "
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "ZeroLeadingSequenceNumber",
          "marks": [
            {
              "type": "code"
            }
          ]
        },
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": " function is a scalar function in Microsoft SQL Server designed to format a sequence number by adding leading zeros to it. This function is typically used to ensure that sequence numbers have a consistent length, which can be important for sorting, display, or integration purposes."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "2. Complexity Level: Low"
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "paragraph",
      "content": [
        {
          "type": "text",
          "text": "The function is straightforward, focusing on string manipulation to pad a numeric value with leading zeros. It does not involve complex logic or multiple steps, making it easy to understand and implement."
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "attrs": {
        "level": 1
      },
